# Generate random points
    points = np.random.randint(-RANGE, RANGE, (SIZE, 2))

    # Perform K-means clustering
    kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters=CLUSTERS, random_state=0).fit(points)

    # Create scatter plot
    for i in range(CLUSTERS):
        # Plot clustered data points for each cluster
        plt.scatter(points[kmeans.labels_ == i, 0], points[kmeans.labels_ == i, 1], s=50, alpha=0.5, label=f"Cluster {i}")

        plt.scatter(
            kmeans.cluster_centers_[i, 0],
            kmeans.cluster_centers_[i, 1],
            marker="X",
            c="r",
            s=100,
            label=f"Centroid {i}",
        )

    plt.legend()
    plt.show()

    return points, kmeans
